# 08. Injecting Primitive, String and Collection Properties

**File Name:** `08-Injecting-Primitive-String-And-Collection-Properties.md`

## Introduction

Spring Setter Injection can be used to inject:

- Primitive Data Types
- String Data Types
- Collection Data Types

Spring injects these values using the `<property>` tag.

---

## Injecting Primitive and String Properties

### Student Class

```java
public class Student {

    private String stuName;
    private int studId;
    private double avgOfMarks;
    private short passedOutYear;
    private boolean isSelected;

    // Getters and Setters
}
```

### Bean Configuration

```xml
<bean id="studentOne" class="com.naresh.hello.Student">

    <property name="stuName" value="Dilip"/>
    <property name="studId" value="101"/>
    <property name="avgOfMarks" value="99.88"/>
    <property name="passedOutYear" value="2022"/>
    <property name="isSelected" value="true"/>

</bean>
```

### Property Attributes

#### name

Bean variable name.

```xml
name="stuName"
```

#### value

Actual value to inject.

```xml
value="Dilip"
```

### Internal Execution

```java
Student studentOne = new Student();

studentOne.setStuName("Dilip");
studentOne.setStudId(101);
studentOne.setAvgOfMarks(99.88);
studentOne.setPassedOutYear((short)2022);
studentOne.setSelected(true);
```

### Output

```text
101
Dilip
2022
99.88
true
```

